\simple_sprite{
    A simple sprite object with frames corresponding to a specific image in the folder.
    
    The sprite is displaced downwards by 5 % of the screen height.
    This is useful for animations that want to movet the sprite upwards.
    \y_offset{0.05}
    A constant factor the sprite is scaled by.
    \scale{1.0}
    
    Associates each frame id with the image shown.
    \frame{neutral}{neutral.png}
    \frame{happy}{happy.png}
    \frame{sad}{sad.png}
}
